# Python Code Rules

- Python 3.12+ with strict typing
- ALL functions must have: type hints on every param and return, Google-style docstring, at least one unit test
- async-first: all I/O functions are async. Use `asyncio.to_thread()` for blocking libraries
- Never use `requests` or `urllib` — use `httpx` (async)
- Never use bare `except:` — always catch specific exceptions
- Import order: stdlib → third-party → local (absolute from project root)
- snake_case for functions/variables, PascalCase for classes, SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- Config access: `from config import get_settings; settings = get_settings()`
- Memory access: always through `MemoryManager` — never access tiers directly
- Prompts: all prompt strings ONLY in `llm/prompt_builder.py`
- Tools: must have `execute()` and `dry_run()` methods
- Agents: must register in `agents/registry.py`
